{"by":"rmonvfer","id":47744675,"parent":47738883,"text":"As a Spaniard, this also happens to me. You can either use a VPN or just switch DNS servers to one that doesn’t have anycast nodes in Spain.<p>Cloudflare’s authoritative DNS uses EDNS Client Subnet (ECS) to return different IP pools based on where the query originates. Spanish resolvers get IPs from a range that La Liga blocks. If your recursive resolver is physically outside Spain (or you use DoH&#x2F;DoT to tunnel to one), Cloudflare returns a different, unblocked pool.<p>AdGuard DNS works well for this.","time":1776029108,"type":"comment"}